  "texts": [
    "54 The diffusion-of-innovations theory categorizes adopters into groups like innovators and laggards, with the adoption rate affected by social capital.",
    "Key elements influencing diffusion include the innovation itself, adopters, communication channels, time, and the social system.",
    "54 Rapid diffusion is more likely when a technology is compatible, available to trial, offers relative advantages, is observable and simple to use.",
    "These factors may also apply to biotechnologies such as AI-enabled biological tools, considering aspects like protocol simplicity.",
    "55 The combination of maturation and availability gives a more comprehensive view of the life cycle of the tools assessed in this report in terms of how the tool is developed, funded, and advanced versus how the tool is utilized, adopted and received."
  ]
}